@startuml AcademicPortal_Deployment
title Deployment Diagram - University Academic Portal
left to right direction

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA

skinparam node {
  BackgroundColor white
  BorderColor #444444
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #E8F0FE
  BorderColor #3B82F6
}
skinparam cloud {
  BackgroundColor #ECFDF3
  BorderColor #22C55E
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFFBEA
  BorderColor #D4B106
}

node "Client Device\n(Mobile / Laptop)" as Client {
  artifact "Google Chrome" as Chrome
  artifact "Mozilla Firefox" as Firefox
  artifact "PDF Reader" as PDF
  artifact "Antivirus" as AV
}

node "Router" as Router
node "Firewall" as Firewall
cloud "Cloud / Internet" as Internet

node "Web Server" as WebServer {
  artifact "Apache / Nginx" as WebStack
  artifact "PHP 8.2" as PHP
  artifact "Laravel 12" as Laravel
  artifact "Vue 3 + Inertia" as Vue
  artifact "Academic Portal Application" as App
}

node "Database Server" as DBServer {
  database "MySQL\nacademic_portal" as DB
}

node "Backup Server" as BackupServer {
  database "MySQL Backup\nacademic_portal" as BackupDB
}

Client --> Router : HTTPS / TCP/IP
Router --> Firewall : TCP/IP
Firewall --> Internet : Secured traffic
Internet --> WebServer : HTTPS

WebServer --> DBServer : MySQL Protocol
DBServer --> BackupServer : VPN\nBackup / Replication

note right of Client
**Users**
Students, lecturers, and administrators
access the Academic Portal using
Chrome or Firefox on laptops
or mobile devices.
end note

note right of WebServer
**Application Stack**
Hosts the web application using
Apache/Nginx, PHP 8.2, Laravel 12,
and Vue 3 + Inertia.
end note

note bottom of DBServer
**Primary Data Store**
Stores users, students, courses,
subjects, grades, fees, assignments,
timetables, attendance, announcements,
messages, and notifications.
end note

note right of BackupServer
**Disaster Recovery**
Receives secured database backups
from the primary database server
through VPN to reduce data loss.
end note

@enduml